sentences: Micael Kiriakos Delaoglou (born 31 October 1957), known professionally as Mikkey Dee, is a Swedish rock musician and multi-instrumentalist.
He is best known as the last drummer for British rock band Motörhead from 1991 until its dissolution following the death of Lemmy in December 2015.

Dee is famous for lengthy drum solos, often lasting between five and fifteen minutes.
King Diamond (1985–1989)
Having moved to Copenhagen, Denmark to play with Geisha, Dee joined King Diamond in 1985.
He played on the King Diamond recordings Fatal Portrait (1986), Abigail (1987) and Them (1988).

Dee joined Don Dokken for his solo album Up from the Ashes (1990).

"Following Lemmy's death in December 2015, Dee announced that Motörhead had disbanded.
Scorpions (2016–present)
Dee joined Thin Lizzy to play on their anniversary shows in January 2016.
However, on 19 April, it was announced that he would not be participating.
He was endorsed by Vic Firth, but recently switched to Wincent, with whom he has his own signature model.
He also used Remo heads in the past.
In 2019, Dee opened a rock bar in Paris named Alabama.
